SIMPLE: enforce
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enforce
<hw>En*force"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enforced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enforcing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF.
<ets>enforcier</ets> to strengthen, force, F. <ets>enforcir</ets>; pref.
<ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + F. <ets>force</ets>. See
<er>Force</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put force upon; to force; to
constrain; to compel; <as>as, to <ex>enforce</ex> obedience to
commands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Inward joy <qex>enforced</qex> my heart to smile.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make or gain by force; to obtain by force;
<as>as, to <ex>enforce</ex> a passage</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Enforcing</xex> furious way.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To put in motion or action by violence; to
drive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As swift as stones⟦br⟧
<qex>Enforced</qex> from the old Assyrian slings.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To give force to; to strengthen; to invigorate; to
urge with energy; <as>as, to <ex>enforce</ex> arguments or
requests</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Enforcing</qex> sentiment of the thrust humanity.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To put in force; to cause to take effect; to give
effect to; to execute with vigor; <as>as, to <ex>enforce</ex> the
laws</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To urge; to ply hard; to lay much stress
upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Enforce</qex> him with his envy to the people.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enforce</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enforce
<hw>En*force</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
attempt by force.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To prove; to evince.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To strengthen; to grow strong.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enforce</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Enforce
<hw>En*force"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Force; strength; power.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A petty enterprise of small <qex>enforce</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enforceable</ent>⟦br⟧
